                <head>353. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>Prime Minister Pipinelis resigned on September 26 following protests by the
                    Center Union that his links with <gloss target="#t_ERE1">ERE</gloss> and the
                    repeated election law violations during the 1961 campaign necessitated a neutral
                    figure at the head of the Greek Government during national elections. King
                        <persName>Paul</persName> asked the President of the Supreme Court,
                    Stylianos Mavromichalies, to form a government to oversee elections.
                    Mavromichalies presented his government to Parliament on September 28 and
                    announced that the King would call new elections for November 3.</p>
            </div>
